Traffic analysis zones in the Hamilton CMA.

Source: R/envsocty3LT3-package.R
hamilton_taz.Rd

A table with the traffic analysis zones in the Hamilton CMA, using the GTA06 system. Traffic analysis zones are zoning systems designed for transportation studies. This file is a portion of the system used by the Transportation Tomorrow Survey in the Greater Toronto and Hamilton Area. The object is projected as UTM Zone 17N.

data(hamilton_taz)

Format

A simple features object with 297 rows and 8 variables:

ID

Unique identifier for traffic analysis zones

Area

Surface area of zone in sq.km

GTA06

Unique identifier of zone in the GTA06 system

geometry

Geometry column

Source

Transportation Tomorrow Survey (http://dmg.utoronto.ca/transportation-tomorrow-survey/tts-introduction)
